abstract_ssm: Certificates and diplomas issued to members of the O'Mahoney family of Brooklyn, including Anna, Catherine, Mary, and May O'Mahoney, for passing various stages of academic achievement during the period 1906 to 1925.  Some certificates issued to Anna and Catherine O'Manhoney give them license to teach at the grade school level.  Most of the certificates are issued by the Department of Education of the City of New York, as well as St. Francis Xavier's Academy and various other primary and secondary schools.
